{
  "texts": [
    "Interestingly, in the first recipe, most changes were related to the structure of the recipe, for example: \"I added the ingredients list and made it step by instructions.",
    "I made these steps to make it easier to follow.\"",
    "Whereas in the second and third recipes, most comments referred to the specificity of the instructions and the steps, for example, one participant of G A N R mentioned: \"I described exactly when to move onto a next step and what to look out for in a mixture in order to proceed\".",
    "In summary, we reject H3-1 as we did not see the groups with reflection prompts spending more time revising.",
    "Moreover, our quantitative and qualitative analyses support H3-2 indicating that groups with adaptive feedback perceive the example recipe and annotations as relevant, while suggestions for the other groups started to feel redundant."
  ]
}